Diagnostics are an area of the compiler that could do with a lot of improvement.

:heart:

```
#![feature(main)]
#[main]
fn main1(){}
#[main]
fn main2(){}
```

Another file won't work, `main` is supposed to be toplevel.

@michaelsproul that sounds great!

I might also start adding more diagnostics later this week, too.

Btw, since you're coordinating these, feel free to ping me when one of them needs an r+, or if you plan on rolling them up (and asking me for an r+ on your rolled up PR) :smile:

Ah, my bad. I got E0079 to trigger though! Does triggering both E0079 and E0308 count?

```
enum Foo {
    Q = "32"
}

fn main() {
}
```

Simple reproduction for 387 here, since I doubt I'll get time to do it.

```
fn bar<F: Fn()>(f: F) { }

fn foo() {
    let mut x = 0i32;
    bar(|| x = 2);
}
```

Here's a reproduction of E0390 for anyone that wants it. The error looks quite general (so this is certianly not exhaustive) and I'm probably not qualified to write diagnostics about it:

```
struct Foo {
    x: i32
}
impl *mut Foo { }
```

(edit: although if anyone cares to mentor me on this one that would be cool too :-) )

OK, it's clearly time for me to admit that I'm not going to find time to get 321 done - apologies!  Reproduction below:

aux321.rs:

```
#![feature(optin_builtin_traits)]
pub trait DefaultedTrait { } 
impl DefaultedTrait for .. { }
```

321.rs:

```
extern crate aux321;

use aux321::DefaultedTrait;
struct C;

impl DefaultedTrait for C { } 
impl <'a> DefaultedTrait for &'a C { } 
impl DefaultedTrait for Box<C> { }
```

---

> rustc --crate-type=lib aux321.rs
> rustc --crate-type=lib -L . 321.rs

Should yield E0321.

@AlisdairO: Thanks! I'll write in the next days then.

PS: I post the RFC here: https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/blob/master/text/0019-opt-in-builtin-traits.md#default-and-negative-impls
And more information here: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/e3cd87241898cd88e4348e9c6142a03d8909c4e0/src/librustc_typeck/coherence/orphan.rs#L295-L318
